ass=title> Might have met my first scammer</span><hr size=1> I would like to warn everyone of a kind od trading that in itself isn't dishonest, but makes it much easier to scam people.<br>
<br>
It's that whole I-won't-tell-you-what-I-am-trading-look-in-my-bags-instead business that has started to be common at the EC marketplace.<br>
<br>
I met one of those yesterday. She put up three full bags in my tradewindow, so I could see if anything interested me. I asked for the price on a few items, and the price on the Gatorscale Leggings seemed fine, so I agreeed to buy them. But when she opened the real tradewindow with just my money and the items I was buying, then it was a pair of mammoth hide leggings. She insisted, of course, that it had been mammothhide all along, and since I had only looked at them in a tradewindow and she had reffered to them as &quot;the leggings&quot; there was no evidence at all that she ever had put up gatorscale leggings for trade.<br>
<br>
She claimed that it was my misstake, not hers, and I won't even name her name because she MIGHT have been right. I am, however, VERY suspicious. Her price was in the gatorscale pricerange, far above what anyone have ever gotten for mammoth hide, and while I was very tired (past midnight and all) I don't want to believe that I made that kind of misstake.<br>
<br>
Of course I clicked cancel, there was no harm done.<br>
But I would still like to warn everyone to be VERY VERY careful when they trade with people who don't name the speciffic items they are trading but instead show them by the truckload as bags in tradewindows. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utordor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tordor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/13/00 7:09:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/t64068?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Might have met my first scammer</span><hr size=1> You are being too kind.  The classic 'bait and switch' has been around mostly by stupid newbies who don't realize the dire consequences of being labeled as a scammer.  Leggins that look the same, a shiny brass shield instead of the charred guardian shield etc.  You were correct to examine and dispute the switch and to post it here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/13/00 8:00:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Might have met my first scammer</span><hr size=1> Mmmm, that scam was a real plague back in the old days when you could actually replace items with each other without closing or emptying the tradewindow in between.<br>
<br>
The problem here is not the anicent scam in itself, but that this new trading method makes it so easy for the scammers to cover their tracks.<br>
<br>
I have seen many people do the come-and-look-at-my-backpacks, and most of them are NOT scammers. The method in itself seems effective, but it's quite new new to me. Perhaps it gained popularity recently, perhaps It's just that I am new to trading.<br>
<br>
Anyway:<br>
Always be extra careful when dealing with theese merchants.<br>
